IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDescription: THE GREATER PHOENIX ECONOMIC COUNCIL ATTRACTS QUALITY BUSINESSES TO THE GREATER PHOENIX REGION FROM AROUND THE WORLD, AND ADVOCATES AND CHAMPIONS FOUNDATIONAL EFFORTS TO IMPROVE THE REGION'S COMPETITIVENESS.
IRS990.MissionDescription: ORGANIZATION'S MISSION IS TO ATTRACT QUALITY BUSINESSES TO THE GREATER PHOENIX REGION FROM AROUND THE WORLD, AND TO ADVOCATE AND CHAMPION FOUNDATIONAL EFFORTS TO IMPROVE THE REGION'S COMPETITIVENESS.
IRS990.Description: During FY 2010, GPEC influenced the outcome of $89.3 million in incremental payroll comprising 2,400 new jobs of which 527 were high-paying at an average salary of $55,000. We had 8 technology assists with a total of 209 prospects, 34 of which were international. We achieved a total editorial reach of 479 million with an estimated value of $15 million.

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, line 11
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: Management prepares the Form 990 with assistance from its external auditors. The Audit Committee reviews and approves the Form 990. The Audit Committee reviews the Form 990 with the Executive Committee. The Form 990 is approved.

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, line 12c
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: The Board members are required to update the conflict of interest statement annually.

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, line 15
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: The Executive Committee approves the CEO's compensation. The Committee uses external comparison information for like organizations to ensure that the CEO's compensation is appropriate.

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: Form 990, Part VI, Section C, line 19
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: GOVERNING DOCUMENTS, CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY, AND FINANCIAL STATEMENTS ARE AVAILABLE THROUGH THE ORGANIZATION'S WEBSITE AND UPON REQUEST.
Greater Phoenix Economic Council has a committee that assumes responsibility for oversight of the audit of its financial statements and selection of an independent accountant.
